<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1332.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-04"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 4, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 16th ultimo, No. 897,
                            together with its accompanying copies of the correspondence between Earl
                            Russell and yourself upon the <pb facs="0342" n="302" xml:id="pg_302"/>
                            subject of the sale of the Alexandra, <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> the
                            Mary, at Nassau, has been received, and is approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>